    {
      "id": "10",
      "name": "Description",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "story",
          "data": {
            "list": [
              {
                "desc": "<p>A tool often used for urban construction and ruin exploration in the past.</p><p>Often used to measure angles, it also possessed a state of the art ability to measure and estimate distance.</p><p>Relying on precisely crafted special arrows and the hands of trained professionals,</p><p>It could keep the flight trajectory of arrows as straight as light itself.</p><p></p><p>In addition to planning and construction, it also often came in handy for exploration and even criminal investigations.</p><p>In skilled hands, its distance measurements could be highly accurate.</p><p>During past explorations of the ruins of Remuria, the exploration teams often brought this range gauge along,</p><p>Mostly to locate the historic sites buried by time and destruction.</p><p>Even the modern Hurlock novels that gained great popularity later on,</p><p>Would feature it in a story about locating a secret chamber.</p><p></p><p>Presently, many range gauges are gathering dust on the shelves of antique shops or attic cellars.</p><p>As more and more similar tools with greater ease-of-use and a lower skill requirement came into general use,</p><p>The production of special arrows has completely ceased, and they too were soon lost and forgotten.</p><p>However, as the gauge remains a longbow that can be carried around without arousing any suspicion or questioning,</p><p>It has been used for several purposes beyond its original design during some certain tumultuous times. </p>",
                "title": ""
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
